SIMPLE: made-up
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: made-up
<hw>made-up</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>formed or conceived by
the imagination; not true; <as>as, a <ex>made-up</ex>
story</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fabricated, fancied, fictional, fictitious,
invented.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having been paved.</def> <mark>[British]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>marked by the use of cosmetic makeup; <as>as,
heavily <ex>made-up</ex> eyes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>formed by fitting or joining components
together.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> assembled, built(prenominal).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Madge</ent>⟦br⟧
